text-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;_Hlk129864948&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;Notwithstanding the first reason
for refusal, a Section 106 Agreement to secure contribution towards Epping
Forest mitigation measures generated by the proposal have not been forthcoming.
In the absence of this, the proposal is considered contrary to Policy DF1 of
the London Plan (2021), and Policies DM1 and DM36 of the Waltham Forest Local
Plan Development Management Policies (2013).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
text-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;Notwithstanding the first reason for refusal, a
Section 106 Agreement to provide sufficient mitigation against any potential
car parking pressure generated by the proposal have not been forthcoming. In the
absence of this, the proposal is considered contrary to Policy CS7 of the
Waltham Forest Local Plan Core Strategy (2012), and Policies DM16 and DM36 of
the Waltham Forest Local Plan Development Management Policies (2013).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
text-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;Notwithstanding the first reason for refusal, insufficient
cycle storage is provided for the number of dwellings contrary to Policy T5 of
the London Plan (2021) and Policy DM16 of the Waltham Forest Local Plan Development
Management Policies (2013).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
margin-left:0cm;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;Notwithstanding the first reason for refusal, the
proposed development would provide a poor standard of living accommodation and have
an adverse impact on the amenity of the future occupiers in terms of loss of
privacy, contrary to Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021), Policy CS15 of the
Waltham Forest Local Plan Core Strategy (2012), Policy DM7 of the Waltham
Forest Local Plan Development Management Policies (2013), and the Urban Design
SPD (2010).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
text-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;Notwithstanding the first reason for refusal, the
amenity space adjoining No. 528 Lea Bridge Road would have a significant
harmful impact on neighbouring amenity in terms of loss of privacy and loss of daylight/sunlight
penetration contrary to Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021), Policy DM32 of the
Waltham Forest Local Plan Development Management Policies (2013), the Urban
Design SPD (2010), and the Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2010).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
text-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;Notwithstanding the first reason for refusal, due
to the locality of the properties the proposed unit mix is not appropriate which,
together with the loss of commercial floorspace along the ground floor level, does
not optimise the capacity of the site. As such, the proposal conflicts with
Policies D3 and H10 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy DM5 of the Waltham
Forest Local Plan Development Management Policies (2013).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
margin-left:0cm;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;The properties are located within Restricted
Dwelling Conversion Ward of Lea Bridge Ward Therefore, the conversion of the existing
3-bedroom dwellings into smaller self-contained flats is contrary to Policies
CS2, DM5 and DM6 of the Local Plan and is unacceptable in principle.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
